^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|I think both the auction and play were fine, but I will just make a few clarifications.  elizabeth's bid was DONT, showing diamonds and a major.  I think she is a bit weak to do it vulnerable, but since all her points are in her 2 suits, and she has a singleton, there is some merit to her bid. My responsiblity as responder to DONT is to pass with 3+ card diamond support, otherwise to bid the next higher suit at two level --2@H here, which allows partner to pass if she has hearts or bid spades if she has spades. In this case I had 3 diamonds, so I passed. Then, I think it is reasonable for terry to show his 5 card spade suit. It turns out 2@S is down, but on average roberta will have a better hand, and it will make or go down 1  and we probably make 2@D anyway, so no big loss.|
