hondo717: |cp||at|Yes, that is a good point. roberta should actually ask about the Q of hearts, by bidding 5@D over my 5@C. Since I do have the Q of hearts, I respond 6@C, which is the cheapest King that I have. Further, roberta need not bid 4@D because she knows we have control of all the suits, so RKCB is her correct bid.|
PG| ***** 70 ***** |


nt||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|And regarding the "specific kings" question, if roberta asks about the Q of hearts by bidding 5@D over 5@C, responses are as follows:
- if I do not have the Q of hearts, I bid 5@H;
- if I do have the Q of hearts, I bid the lowest suit in which I have a king, in this case clubs
- if I have the Q of hearts but no outside kings, I bid 5N (some people play I bid 6@H.)

Now, let me focus on the play of the hand.|
