nt||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Slam is a very good contract. roberta can count 11 top tricks, 5 hearts, 2 diamonds, 3 spades and 1 club and she needs to develop a 12th trick. There are a couple of possibilities. One is, if terry has the ace of clubs, she has 2 club tricks. The other is, if spades are 4-3, she can make her 5th spade good. She can also ruff a club high, if clubs are 3-2. But if clubs are 4-1, she can go down. In any case, at trick 2 she has to do one of the following:
- she either has to play ace of spades and ruff a spade, and then draw trumps ending in dummy or,
- she has to draw trumps ending in dummy, and then play a club, keeping the ace of spades as a 2nd entry.|
PG| ***** 72 ***** |


nt||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Basically, since she decided to draw trumps first, she then has to play a club before playing spades. It turns out either play works, clubs or spades, and she has to pick one. Again it comes down to counting your winners and losers before playing out the hand. |cs|4|at|^-
