^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Another interesting bidding hand. Let me discuss it before we start the play. The first two bids are pretty standard. As to roberta's one spade bid, one level overcalls only require 8 points or so. Some people prefer you have a better suit, as partner will be leading it. However, the modern tendency is to lay claim to the spade suit if you have it, so roberta's bid has some merit. And, about my 4@C bid. Once partner bids 1@H, I know we should be in at least 4 hearts. And it turns out, you can splinter as opener, if you have a game forcing hand, support for partner, and a singleton.|
